sample_comments.text:
The good:
- Hotel grounds were expansive and had a nice relaxing atmosphere;
- Located midpoint between the town centre and the seafood restaurant cluster;

The bad:
- Almost everything was chargeable, including bottled water in the room and floats at the pool;
- The room was in a rather bad condition, the shower was intermittently hot/cold, the television was quite old (CRT!) with rather bad reception, etc...;
- There was at least a power outage a day!
- Food at the only restaurant was very average but overpriced;
- Service certainly wasn't great;

Overall, we had a pleasant stay; We stayed only for 1 night, as the following day we had booked a diving trip at Rayong Dive Center to Koh Talu and returned home to Ayuthaya after the diving trip;
However there was 1 thing which we didn't noticed when booking this hotel; 
The room rates are excluding the breakfast buffet; 
Ofcourse break fast is available for a charge os 350 Baht per person; :(
